'''Anthony J. Tata''', known as '''Tony Tata'''({{IPAc-en|t|e<U+026A>|<U+02C8>|t|<U+0259>}}), has served as Secretary of Transportation of the [[U.S. State]] of [[North Carolina]] since January, 2013.  As Secretary of Transportation, he is the head of the [[North Carolina Department of Transportation]], and also a member of the [[North Carolina Cabinet]].  Previously, he served as the Chief Operating Officer of the [[District of Columbia Public Schools]] (from 2009-2010) and Superintendent of the [[Wake County Public School System]] (from 2010-2012).  He is a former [[brigadier general]] in the [[United States Army]], having served for 28 years in the military before retiring in 2009.  From 2006-2007 he was Deputy Commanding General of U.S. forces in Afghanistan. <ref>{{cite news|last=Siceloff|first=Bruce|title=He's not 'The General,' but he's the boss at DOT|url=http://www.newsobserver.com/2013/01/07/2589460/road-worrier-hes-not-the-general.html|accessdate=22 January 2013|newspaper=[[The News & Observer]]|date=8 January 2013}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news|last=Frank|first=John|title=McCrory completes Cabinet, names Tata in another surprising pick|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/2013/01/04/3762753/tony-tata-named-nc-transportation.html|accessdate=22 January 2013|newspaper=[[The Charlotte Observer]]|date=4 January 2013|author2=T. Keung Hui}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NCDOT Leadership: Secretary of Transportation|url=http://www.ncdot.gov/about/leadership/secretary.html|accessdate=22 January 2013}}</ref>

